          "Models",
          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Probability of getting the next candidate exercise correct",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "3852 ASSISTments09 learners, 27485 ASSISTments12 learners nad 5000 EdNet learners",
          "ASSISTments & EdNet",
          "Answer sequences",
          "[Question, Skill and Exercise Embeddings]",
          "Previous models often compute the learners’ current state as a weighted sum aggregation of all historical states based on correlation between current question and historical questions → all previous knowledge states are considered.",
          "The model GIKT uses attention to select which previous states should be considered for the computation of new question performance. Moreover, it is, to the authors’ knowledge to evaluate question-skills relationships via Graph Neural Networks.",
          "The model creates 3 embedding matrices that represent questions, skills and answers.\n\nQuestion-skill relationships are modelled using a Knowledge Graph. \n\nThe model incorporates the concept of mastery of a question by the student. This mastery is determined from the history of interactions with similar questions. ",
          "BKT, KTM, DKT, DKVMN, DKT-Q, DKT-QS, GAKT",
          "Holdout Method",
          "AST09\n{AUC: 0.7896 - GIKT}\n\nAST12\n{AUC: 0.7754 - GIKT}\n\nEddNet\n{AUC: 0.7523 - GIKT}",
          "Authors propose a new model and validate it using 3 datasets. The authors perform a set of Ablation studies to show how parameter optimization impacts the performance of the models.\n\n",
          "No testing on Cold-Start Scenario.\n\nNo Cross-Validation.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
